values.content:
=Analyze this LinkedIn profile and return a JSON object with these fields:
- lead_score (1-10, based on how likely they are to buy AI automation services)
- pain_points (array of 2-3 likely business pain points)
- personalization_hook (one sentence ice-breaker for outreach)
- recommended_service (which automation service would help them most)

Profile:
Name: {{ $json.fullName }}
Title: {{ $json.headline }}
Company: {{ $json.companyName }}
Summary: {{ $json.summary }}

Return ONLY valid JSON.

parameters.jsCode:
const lead = $('Apify LinkedIn Scraper').item.json;
let enrichment = {};
try { enrichment = JSON.parse($input.first().json.content[0].text); } catch(e) {}
return [{ json: {
  full_name: lead.fullName,
  headline: lead.headline,
  company: lead.companyName,
  linkedin_url: lead.linkedinUrl,
  location: lead.location,
  lead_score: enrichment.lead_score || 0,
  pain_points: (enrichment.pain_points || []).join('; '),
  personalization_hook: enrichment.personalization_hook || '',
  recommended_service: enrichment.recommended_service || '',
  scraped_date: new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]
}}];
